quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  15,91,"those who have made the Recital<a class=""sup""><sup>f </sup></a>into fragments."
  15,92,"So by your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord, We will surely ask them all"
  15,93,"about what they used to do."
  15,94,"So proclaim<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>openly what you are commanded and disregard the polytheists."
  15,95,"Indeed, We have sufficed you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>against the mockers:"
  15,96,"those who set up another god with Allah. So they will come to know."
  15,97,"And most surely We are aware that your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>chest tightens with what they say."
  15,98,"So exalt your Lord with praise and be of those who prostrate,"
  15,99,"and worship your Lord until Certitude{1}comes to you.",footnotes:1:According to Salem Ibn ‘Abdullah and other exegetes this means death.
  16,1,"Allah’s command has come, so do<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>not rush it. Highly Exalted is He, and Most High above what <span class=""h"">they<sup foot_note=""80373"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">associate</span><i class=""s"">(with Him) </i>."
  16,2,"<span class=""h"">He</span><span class=""h"">bestows<sup foot_note=""80374"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">the angels from on high</span>with the Spirit by His command upon whom He wills of His servants: “Give<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>warning that there is no god but Me, so be mindful of Me.”"
  16,3,"He created the heavens and the earth with truth. Most High is He above what they associate<i class=""s"">(with Him) </i>."
  16,4,"He created man from a sperm-drop, yet he becomes an evident adversary!"
  16,5,"And livestock—He created them for you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>. In them are warmth and benefits for you, and of them you eat."
  16,6,"And there is beauty in them for you when you drive them home and when you drive them to pasture."
